Description: Analysis of Blood-Oxygen-Level-Dependent (BOLD) fMRI data for
    sleep and circadian research. Receives preprocessed derivatives from
    fMRIPrep and transforms them into analysis-ready outputs: atlas-agnostic
    parcellation with an extensible atlas schema, ROI-level timeseries
    extraction, voxelwise signal metrics (tSNR, GLM contrasts), and
    functional connectivity matrices. Exports parcellated BOLD data directly
    to syncR for integration with actigraphy, polysomnography, and
    questionnaire data in a unified participant-indexed database. Part of
    the Circadia Lab R ecosystem at Northumbria University.
    fmriprep gets you clean data. boldR gets you useful data.
